e>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=RES-173-27-0161"><gtr:id>64721A58-BCA4-4F80-A774-66F9FBDB307A</gtr:id><gtr:title>Responding to the Council for Science &amp;amp; Technology Report How Academia &amp;amp; Government Can Work Together</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>RES-173-27-0161</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>&lt;p>The Placement Fellowship will take forward recommendations made in the Council for Science and Technology (CST) report &lt;em>How Academia and Government can Work Together&lt;/em> [CST (2008) &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cst.gov.uk/cst/reports/#Academia&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;>www.cst.gov.uk/cst/reports/#Academia&lt;/a>]. It will develop an action plan that sets out how the reports recommendations to Government will be implemented. The Fellowship will assist in co-ordinating delivery of the action plan from the Government Office for Science in partnership with key stakeholders.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The CST Report identifies opportunities to promote the use of academic research in policy making. The report's recommendations to academia and Government focus on action in three areas:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>Building relationships and communication &lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Building capacity to ensure a more productive engagement &lt;/li>

 &lt;li>Valuing and rewarding engagement&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>The action plan identifies new approaches to be piloted and opportunities to enhance ongoing activities with the aim of strengthening engagement between academic research and Government policy making. The pilots will be reviewed by the Government Office for Science and an initial report on what has been learned will be published by the summer of 2010.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The action plan also aims to enhance communication among key stakeholders to promote more co-ordinated, coherent and effective approaches to strengthening engagement between academia and Government.&lt;/p>

